1 residential property, any annual assessment imposed on such qualifying
2 property that becomes delinquent, including any interest on the annual
3 assessment and any penalty, shall constitute a PACE lien against the
4 qualifying property on which the annual assessment is imposed until the
5 annual assessment, including any interest and penalty, is paid in full.
6 Any annual assessment that is not paid within the time period set forth
7 in the assessment contract shall be considered delinquent. The
8 municipality shall, within fourteen days after an annual assessment
9 becomes delinquent or, if there is a third-party lender financing the
10 energy project, within fourteen days after receiving notice from such
11 third-party lender that an annual assessment has become delinquent,
12 record a notice of such lien in the office of the register of deeds of
13 the county in which the qualifying property is located. The municipality
14 shall certify the amount of any such delinquency and lien to the county
15 treasurer, and the lien shall be treated as a special assessment in the
16 same manner as special assessments are treated under section 77-1858 and
17 shall be subject to the same collection processes for real estate taxes
18 and special assessments as set forth in Chapter 77, including, without
19 limitation, sections 77-1801 to 77-1863.
20 (b) For qualifying property that is single-family residential
21 property, all annual assessments imposed on such qualifying property,
22 including any interest on the annual assessments and any penalty, shall,
23 upon the initial annual assessment, constitute a PACE lien against the
24 qualifying property on which the annual assessments are imposed until all
25 annual assessments, including any interest and penalty, are paid in full.
26 Any annual assessment that is not paid within the time period set forth
27 in the assessment contract shall be considered delinquent. The
28 municipality shall, upon imposition of the initial annual assessment,
29 record a notice of such lien in the office of the register of deeds of
30 the county in which the qualifying property is located.
