2 Sec. 8. Section 18-2101.02, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
3 amended to read:
4 18-2101.02 (1) For any city that (a) intends to prepare a
5 redevelopment plan that will divide ad valorem taxes for a period of more
6 than fifteen years but not more than twenty years as provided in
7 subdivision (5)(a) (4)(a) of section 18-2147, (b) intends to declare an
8 area as an extremely blighted area for purposes of funding decisions
9 under subdivision (1)(b) of section 58-708, or (c) intends to declare an
10 area as an extremely blighted area in order for individuals purchasing
11 residences in such area to qualify for the income tax credit authorized
12 in subsection (7) of section 77-2715.07, the governing body of such city
13 shall first declare, by resolution adopted after the public hearings
14 required under this section, such area to be an extremely blighted area.
15 (2) Prior to making such declaration, the governing body of the city
16 shall conduct or cause to be conducted a study or an analysis on whether
17 the area is extremely blighted and shall submit the question of whether
18 such area is extremely blighted to the planning commission or board of
19 the city for its review and recommendation. The planning commission or
20 board shall hold a public hearing on the question after giving notice of
21 the hearing as provided in section 18-2115.01. The planning commission or
22 board shall submit its written recommendations to the governing body of
23 the city within thirty days after the public hearing.
24 (3) Upon receipt of the recommendations of the planning commission
25 or board, or if no recommendations are received within thirty days after
26 the public hearing required under subsection (2) of this section, the
27 governing body shall hold a public hearing on the question of whether the
28 area is extremely blighted after giving notice of the hearing as provided
29 in section 18-2115.01. At the public hearing, all interested parties
30 shall be afforded a reasonable opportunity to express their views
31 respecting the proposed declaration. After such hearing, the governing
-8-

LB1135 LB1135
2026 2026
1 body of the city may make its declaration.
2 (4) Copies of each study or analysis conducted pursuant to
3 subsection (2) of this section shall be posted on the city's public
4 website or made available for public inspection at a location designated
5 by the city.
6 (5) The study or analysis required under subsection (2) of this
7 section may be conducted in conjunction with the study or analysis
8 required under section 18-2109. The hearings required under this section
9 may be held in conjunction with the hearings required under section
10 18-2109.
11 (6) Notwithstanding any other provisions of the Community
12 Development Law, the designation of an area as an extremely blighted area
13 pursuant to this section shall be valid for a period of no less than
14 twenty-five years from the effective date of the resolution declaring
15 such area to be an extremely blighted area, except that such designation
16 may be removed prior to the end of such period pursuant to section
17 18-2156.
