LB1135 LB1135
2026 2026
1 secured by pledges and deposits with a bank or trust company, in trust
2 for the payment of such notes, of bonds in an aggregate amount at least
3 equal to the amount of such notes and, in any event, in an amount deemed
4 by the issuing authority sufficient to provide for the payment of the
5 notes in full at the maturity thereof. The authority may provide in the
6 collateral agreement that the notes may be exchanged for bonds held as
7 collateral security for the notes, or that the trustee may sell the bonds
8 if the notes are not otherwise paid at maturity, and apply the proceeds
9 of such sale to the payment of the notes. Such notes shall bear interest
10 at a rate set by the authority, and shall be sold at such price as shall
11 cause an interest cost thereon not to exceed such rate.
12 It is the intention hereof that any pledge of revenue, income,
13 receipts, proceeds, or other money made by an authority for the payment
14 of bonds or notes shall be valid and binding from the time such pledge is
15 made; that the revenue, income, receipts, proceeds, and other money so
16 pledged and thereafter received by the authority shall immediately be
17 subject to the lien of such pledge without the physical delivery thereof
18 or further act, and that the lien of any such pledge shall be valid and
19 binding as against all parties having claims of any kind in tort,
20 contract, or otherwise against the authority irrespective of whether such
21 parties have notice thereof. Neither the resolution nor any other
22 instrument by which a pledge is created need be recorded.
