17 Meetings Act.
18 (2) All of a land bank's records and documents shall be considered
19 public records for purposes of sections 84-712 to 84-712.09.
20 (3) The board shall provide a report monthly reports to the
21 municipality or municipalities that created the land bank on the board's
22 activities pursuant to the Nebraska Municipal Land Bank Act. The report
23 shall be provided after each meeting of the board or at least quarterly.
24 The board shall also electronically submit provide an annual report to
25 the municipality or municipalities that created the land bank, the
26 Speaker of the Legislature, the chairperson of the Executive Board of the
27 Legislative Council, the Revenue Committee of the Legislature, and the
28 Urban Affairs Committee of the Legislature by March 1 of each year
29 summarizing the board's activities for the prior calendar year. The
30 reports submitted to the Legislature shall be submitted electronically.
31 (4) The annual report required under subsection (3) of this section
-33-

LB1135 LB1135
2026 2026
1 shall include, but not be limited to:
2 (a) A listing of each property owned by the land bank at the end of
3 the prior calendar year, including (i) how long each such property has
4 been owned by the land bank, (ii) and whether such property was acquired
5 utilizing the automatically accepted bid under section 18-3417 or
6 18-3418, (iii) whether such property is being held on behalf of a
7 nonprofit corporation or other private entity pursuant to subsection (8)
8 of section 18-3408, and (iv) the intended use of each property being held
9 on behalf of a nonprofit corporation or other private entity pursuant to
10 subsection (8) of section 18-3408;
11 (b) A list of entities and individuals who received more than two
12 thousand five hundred dollars from the land bank in the prior calendar
13 year;
14 (c) A list of financial institutions in which the land bank has
15 deposited funds;
16 (d) The percentage of total parcels located in each municipality
17 which are held by the land bank; and
18 (e) A statement certifying that all board members and employees of
19 the land bank comply with the conflict of interest requirements in
20 sections 18-3407 and 18-3415.
21 Sec. 20. (1) A city of the primary class, city of the first class,
22 city of the second class, or village may sell or transfer any waterworks,
23 sewer system, or water system owned by such city or village to an Indian
24 tribe if the following requirements are met:
25 (a) The waterworks, sewer system, or water system must be located or
26 operating in its entirety within the tribal lands of such Indian tribe;
27 (b) The tribal headquarters of such Indian tribe must be located in
28 such city or village; and
29 (c) The sale or transfer must be approved by the qualified electors
30 of such city or village at a general or special election described in
31 subsection (2) of this section.
-34-

LB1135 LB1135
2026 2026
1 (2) The governing body of the city or village seeking to sell or
2 transfer any waterworks, sewer system, or water system under this section
3 shall submit such question or proposition, in the usual manner, to the
4 qualified electors of such city or village at any general city or village
5 election or at any special city or village election and may submit the
6 proposition in connection with any city or village special election
7 called for any other purpose, and the votes cast thereon shall be
8 canvassed and the result found and declared as in any other city or
9 village election.
10 (3) For purposes of this section, Indian tribe means an Indian tribe
11 or band which is recognized by federal law or formally acknowledged by
12 the state as of January 1, 2026.
13 Sec. 21. The Revisor of Statutes shall assign section 6 of this act
14 to Chapter 19.
15 Sec. 22. Sections 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15,
16 16, 17, 18, 19, 20, and 24 of this act become operative three calendar
17 months after the adjournment of this legislative session. The other
18 sections of this act become operative on their effective date.
19 Sec. 23. Original section 13-3206, Reissue Revised Statutes of
20 Nebraska, is repealed.
21 Sec. 24. Original sections 18-2124, 18-2125, 18-2136, 18-3404,
22 18-3405, 18-3407, 18-3408, 18-3410, and 18-3413, Reissue Revised Statutes
23 of Nebraska, section 18-2117.01, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
24 2024, and sections 18-2101.02 and 18-2147, Revised Statutes Supplement,
25 2025, are repealed.
26 Sec. 25. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
27 passed and approved according to law.
